  "text": "Despite the high M ORF diversity observed, the evolution of functional domains important in processing and trafficking of the GPC [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] [CITATION_5] [CITATION_6] , appeared to be highly constrained. The furin cleavage site [CITATION_7] is conserved in all strains; the SKI-1 or SKI-1-like protease recognition sites R(R/K)LL located by the Gn N and C termini are completely conserved, as is the R(R/K)PL site located at the N terminus of Gc [CITATION_8] .",
